comments.body:
In 0e5ef5d "net: track received peer in private broadcast"

This seems like a costly(-ier) way to figure out if there is any pending transaction. We can short-circuit early in the iteration.

This diff passes unit tests.
```diff
diff --git a/src/private_broadcast.cpp b/src/private_broadcast.cpp
index f43ebd7eca..42c163bc4a 100644
--- a/src/private_broadcast.cpp
+++ b/src/private_broadcast.cpp
@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@
 #include <util/check.h>
 
 #include <algorithm>
+#include <ranges>
 
 
 bool PrivateBroadcast::Add(const CTransactionRef& tx)
@@ -103,7 +104,9 @@ bool PrivateBroadcast::HavePendingTransactions()
     EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(!m_mutex)
 {
     LOCK(m_mutex);
-    return !GetPendingTransactions().empty();
+    return std::ranges::any_of(m_transactions | std::views::values, [](const TxSendStatus& send_status) {
+        return !send_status.received.has_value();
+    });
 }
 
 std::vector<CTransactionRef> PrivateBroadcast::GetStale() const
```

